    "en": {
      "title": "Last digit of number plate for refuelling revised: Kanchana",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Power and Energy Ministry has announced the revision of the last digit of the number plate for refuelling for vehicles, which will be effective from July 21.",
        "Accordingly, vehicles that have the last digits of 0, 1, and 2 in the number plate will be allowed to get fuel on Tuesday and Saturday. If the number plate's last digit ends with 3,4 or 5, those vehicles will allow for refuelling on Thursdays and Sundays.",
        "Meanwhile, if the last digit of the number plates ends with 6, 7, 8, or 9, those vehicles will allow for refuelling on Mondays, Wednesdays, and Fridays.",
        "Moreover, the Minister said the QR Code will be tested at multiple locations in Colombo from July 21 to 24."
      ],
